Agaju Madugba, Katsina Katsina State Governor, Alhaji Aminu Bello Masari, has described President Muhammadu Buhari as being ready to pay the supreme price, if need be, in a determined effort to return Nigeria to the path of sustainable development. According to the governor, “President Muhammadu Buhari has staked his life for Nigeria and he is ready to pay the supreme price to put the country on the right track.” Hovernor Masari said this on Thursday evening, when a former Governor of Abia State, Dr. Orji Uzor Kalu, led members of his National Movement for the Re-election of Buhari to the Katsina Government House. Masari explained that Buhari’s journey to the Presidency in 2015 was because, “he could not fold his hands when things were going bad for Nigeria.” Details later…